Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 of Hip MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Femoroacetabular impingment (FAI)' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled

And 'CAM morphology' radio button is enabled
And 'Pincer morphology' radio button is enabled

And 'Herniation pit, anterolateral femoral neck' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema at the head/neck transition' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'CAM morphology' radio button
Then 'Cartilage lesion anterior superior/superior' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondrolabral separation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Alpha angle' input field is enabled

When I enter any angle from 56 to 90 in 'Alpha angle' input field
Then 'Decreased offset' automatically filled checkbox is checked

When I select 'Pincer morphology' radio button
Then 'Acetabular overcoverage' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cartilage lesion posterior/posterior inferior' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Herniation pit, anterolateral femoral neck' checkbox
Then 'Fluid isointense' checkbox is enabled
And 'Peripheral sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
